provisions.content:
(a)     ‘authorised officer’ means an officer authorised by a Provincial Government;
(b)     ‘field’ means a khasra number as defined in the Provincial law relating to land
revenue;
(c)     ‘first zone’ means an area adjacent to and beyond the external frontier of
Pakistan extending towards Pakistan to a line at four kilometers measured
from the external frontiers of Pakistan;
(d)     ‘second zone’ means an area adjacent to and beyond the first zone extending
towards Pakistan to a line at four kilometers measured from the first zone ; and
(e)     ‘tree’ means a large plant with a self-supporting trunk.

